Boil a full #kettle{}.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm chunks. Cut the @Tenderstem® broccoli{80%g} into thirds, cutting any thick stems lengthways.

Peel and grate your @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #saucepan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, stir in the garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Pour the @boiled water for the bulgur{220%ml} into the saucepan.

Stir in the @bulgur wheat{120%g} and @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, bring back up to the boil and simmer for ~{1%minute}.

Pop a #lid{} on the pan and remove from the heat. Leave to the side for ~{15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once the oil is hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{240%g}, pepper chunks and the @roasted spice and herb blend{1%sachet}. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, then stir to combine.

Fry until the pepper has softened and the chicken is golden brown and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}. Stir occasionally and lower the heat if needed.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the chicken is cooked, add the Tenderstem® to the pan and stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}, then add a splash of @water{}.

Pop a lid on the pan, or cover in some #foil{}. Cook until tender, a further ~{2-3%minutes}.

Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Once the bulgur is cooked, fluff it up with a #fork{}.

Stir through the @harissa paste{50%g}. Add less if you'd prefer things milder.

Add the harissa bulgur to the chicken and veg pan, then gently mix together until combined.

Spoon the chicken and veg bulgur into your #bowls{}.

Finish with a dollop of @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g}.

Enjoy!